<subSubSection id="C37F6512FF96FFEBFF4C28E0C46E2C20" pageId="11" pageNumber="332" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDA3699FF96FFEBFF4C28E0C46E2C20" blockId="11.[151,1436,151,933]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332">
<emphasis id="B911EA8BFF96FFEBFF4C28E0C7232D98" bold="true" box="[199,321,223,248]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Elytral costa I reaching elytral apex, subapically obliterated; costae II and IV subapically fused, forming an arch, subapically obliterated; costa III not touching the arch formed by costae II+IV (
<figureCitation id="135E2A1CFF96FFEBFB5B293BC3462C7C" box="[1232,1316,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1714,1737]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,204,1685]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,195,1693]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 35. Elytra: 27. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 28. M. quadricostatus; 29. M. caeruleus; 30. M. germaini; 31. M. grandjeani; 32. M. subparallelus; 33. M. testaceirostris; 34. M. simoni; 35. M. kirschi Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271310/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="332">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF96FFEBFA8F293BC3462C7C" box="[1284,1316,260,284]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
). Adjacent area of scutellum black (
<figureCitation id="135E2A1CFF96FFEBFE202918C79D2C20" box="[427,511,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1714,1737]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,204,1685]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,195,1693]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 35. Elytra: 27. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 28. M. quadricostatus; 29. M. caeruleus; 30. M. germaini; 31. M. grandjeani; 32. M. subparallelus; 33. M. testaceirostris; 34. M. simoni; 35. M. kirschi Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271310/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="332">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF96FFEBFE542917C79D2C20" box="[479,511,296,320]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37F6512FF96FFEBFF4C2973C5732E58" pageId="11" pageNumber="332" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDA3699FF96FFEBFF4C2973C3652C95" blockId="11.[151,1436,151,933]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332">
<emphasis id="B911EA8BFF96FFEBFF4C2973C7162C05" bold="true" box="[199,372,332,357]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332">Redescription.</emphasis>
Head black, prolonged in short rostrum, as long as sum of antennomeres II+III (
<figureCitation id="135E2A1CFF96FFEBFABD2973C3EF2C04" box="[1334,1421,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1433,1456]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,198,1400]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,193,1413]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 18. Rostrum: 10. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 11. M. quadricostatus; 12. M. caeruleus; 13. M. germaini; 14. M. grandjeani; 15. M. subparallelus; 16. M. testaceirostris; 17. M. simoni; 18. M. kirschi. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271308/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="332">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF96FFEBFAE42973C3EF2C04" box="[1391,1421,332,356]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
); coronal suture shallow; median interocular distance of 
<date id="FFDB1059FF96FFEBFC98294FC54D2CE8" box="[787,815,368,392]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332">
<number id="3DAD24BEFF96FFEBFC98294FC5432CE8" box="[787,801,368,392]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
width of eyes. Mandibles curved, connate to labrum, testaceous. Maxillary palp with palpomere IV slightly larger than III, securiform; segments II and III subequal in length. Antennae finely pubescent, scape subconic, pedicel small (
<number id="3DAD24BEFF96FFEBFC082987C5EF2CB0" box="[899,909,440,464]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF96FFEBFC132987C5C42CB0" box="[920,934,440,464]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332" value="3.0">3</number>
of scape length); antennomere III as long as I; IV subequal to III, slightly larger and longer; antennomeres V to XI gradually decreasing in length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA3699FF96FFEBFF4C2A3FC22B2FE5" blockId="11.[151,1436,151,933]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332">
Pronotum rectangular, transverse, slightly wider than longer (
<number id="3DAD24BEFF96FFEBFC032A3FC5F52F78" box="[904,919,512,536]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332" value="8.0">8</number>
: 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF96FFEBFC172A3FC5CF2F78" box="[924,941,512,536]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332" value="9.0">9</number>
), with rounded angles and posterior angles pronounced, testaceous, with a longitudinal black stripe medially located; a pair of longitudinal elevations parallels, discontinued at basal and apical third, broadened in middle third. Pair of oblique elevations in basal third and a pair of parallel median elevations (
<figureCitation id="135E2A1CFF96FFEBFDEB2A53C4C72FE4" box="[608,677,620,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,204,1805]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,195,1259]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Dorsal view: 1. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 2. M. quadricostatus; 3. M. caeruleus; 4. M. germaini; 5. M. grandjeani; 6. M. simoni; 7. Macrolygistopterus subparallelus; 8. M. testaceirostris; 9. M. kirschi." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271307/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="332">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF96FFEBFD1F2A53C4C72FE4" box="[660,677,620,644]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Scutellum black, wider than longer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDA3699FF96FFEBFF4C2AB0C7B62E74" blockId="11.[151,1436,151,933]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332">
Elytra subparallel, margins stout and pronounced, testaceous, with apical third black. Arrangement of elytral costae: Elytral costa I reaching elytral apex, subapically obliterated; costae II and IV subapically fused, forming an arch, subapically obliterated; costa III not touching arch formed by costae II+IV (
<figureCitation id="135E2A1CFF96FFEBFBEC2AE8C2A22F90" box="[1127,1216,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1714,1737]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,204,1685]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,195,1693]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 35. Elytra: 27. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 28. M. quadricostatus; 29. M. caeruleus; 30. M. germaini; 31. M. grandjeani; 32. M. subparallelus; 33. M. testaceirostris; 34. M. simoni; 35. M. kirschi Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271310/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="332">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF96FFEBFB2B2AE7C2A22F90" box="[1184,1216,728,752]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
). Adjacent area of scutellum black (
<figureCitation id="135E2A1CFF96FFEBFEDC2AC3C7F92E74" box="[343,411,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,204,1805]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,195,1259]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Dorsal view: 1. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 2. M. quadricostatus; 3. M. caeruleus; 4. M. germaini; 5. M. grandjeani; 6. M. simoni; 7. Macrolygistopterus subparallelus; 8. M. testaceirostris; 9. M. kirschi." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271307/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="332">
Fig. 
<number id="3DAD24BEFF96FFEBFE002AC3C7F92E74" box="[395,411,764,788]" pageId="11" pageNumber="332" value="4.3">4</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="135E2A1CFF96FFEBFE2C2AC3C7A52E74" box="[423,455,764,788]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1714,1737]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,204,1685]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,195,1693]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 35. Elytra: 27. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 28. M. quadricostatus; 29. M. caeruleus; 30. M. germaini; 31. M. grandjeani; 32. M. subparallelus; 33. M. testaceirostris; 34. M. simoni; 35. M. kirschi Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271310/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="332">30</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
